%@2@%%@CR:C6A00010002 @%%@AB@%Before You Proceed%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
Before installing Microsoft C, take a few minutes to make sure your computer
meets minimum system requirements and that your package is complete.  %@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@3@%%@CR:C6A00010003 @%%@AB@%System Requirements%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
Microsoft C requires the following configuration:  %@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   An IBM Personal Computer or 100% compatible running DOS version 3.0 or
      later or OS/2 version 1.1 or later.  %@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   An 8088 processor (a minimum of an 8 megahertz, 80286 processor is
      recommended).%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   512K (kilobytes) of available memory (RAM) for operating under DOS (1
      megabyte of RAM is recommended).%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   3 megabytes of RAM for operating under OS/2 (4 megabytes of RAM are
      recommended).%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   At least 384K of extended memory if you want to debug large DOS
      programs.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   One hard-disk drive with a minimum of 8 megabytes of free space.
      (Depending on the options you want, you may need up to 20 megabytes of
      disk space.)%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş   One 1.2 megabyte, 5.25-inch floppy disk drive or one 720K, 3.5-inch
      floppy disk drive.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
Programs compiled with Microsoft C version 6.0 support DOS versions 2.1 and
later.  %@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
